        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-20 20:01:19.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 11:\n\n(15 comments)\n\n(20 comments)\n•\tFile ONAP-PAP-REST/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/xacml/rest/ConsoleAndApiService.java:\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 196: } catch (Exception e) {\ncan reach line 197 to rollbackTransaction for an exception, let's say from line 194, perhaps from others, but the transaction has been committed already. What would be the behavior to rollback a committed transaction?\nOld code - It checks whether transaction is open before attempting to rollback. It also stops the transaction timer thread.\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 203: response.addHeader(MESSAGE, \"Policy Id is not valid\");\nloggingContext.transactionEnded before returning?\nOld code - No, same as old code (XacmlPapServlet approx. line 1660). It is handled in XacmlPapServlet doPost line: 589.\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 233: } catch (Exception e) {\nNeed to close transaction somehow here from 226 or would be garbagge collected somehow if no updateGroup operation took place?\nOld code - Rollback is done on outer try-catch.\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 254: } catch (Exception e) {\nsimilar question, can line 251 throw exception and try here to rollback a transaction already committed? Questioning to avoid leaks.\nOld code - Rollback won’t be attempted if already commit. PolicyDbDaoTransactionInstance.java line: 284\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 351: } catch (PAPException e) {\nWondering if you can reach this code without all transactions properly closed ? Due to its size is difficult to track scopes of transactions in this method.\nOld code – it looks possible and needs cleanup. But there is a failback mechanism with the transaction timeout thread, created for every transaction, that should do the rollback and close.\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 389: response.setHeader(\"content-type\", \"application/json\");\nis there a reason why in this method, the response stream is closed explicitly but in the previous is not? It is also repeated in several places, the code below, is a good candidate to its own method to reuse.\nOld Code – I don’t see an explicit opening of stream so think it is not needed. The Javadoc of com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper.writeValue() says that it does not close the stream. Maybe original intent was to ensure nothing else gets written except the output json. But don’t  think explicit close would cause problems.\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 394: }\nI see all these transactionEnded but I am not able to match them where they are started, I was expecting to see some loggingContext.transactionStarted(), how does it work?\nOld code – It is passed in from doget() in XacmlPapServlet. This method also used to exist in XacmlPapServlet but in old code also, it was passed in.\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 625: }\ncouldn't json be null here? As exception above prints an error but continues.\nOld code – possible. I don’t see any validation in Policy-sdk-app RestfulPapEngine – sendToPap() either. But it seems to be caught way down in else of “if (pdp != null) {“. Line: 694\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 659: } catch (Exception e) {\nacPutTransaction ended?\nrollback transaction?\nlog transactionEnded?\nOld code – It is handled in outer try-catch line: 792\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 670: } catch (Exception e) {\nsame Qs as before ..\nOld code – It is handled in outer try-catch line: 792\n\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 698: } catch (Exception e) {\ntransaction ended loggging?\nOld code – It is handled in outer try-catch line: 792\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 716: // get the request content into a String\nthis code repeats many times ..\nOld Code – yes, can be extracted to util method.\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 760: } catch (Exception e) {\nrollback transaction? transaction ended?\nOld code – It is handled in outer try-catch line: 792\n•\tFile ONAP-PAP-REST/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/xacml/rest/Heartbeat.java:\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 71: private static final String ISRUNNINGFALSE = \"isRunning is false, getting out of loop.\";\nbetter to mark it private since you have a isHeartbeatRunning() ..\nOld Code – Agree, also Sonar flags it. Fixed.  Same as old XacmlPapServlet.java line: 2462\n•\tFile ONAP-PAP-REST/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/xacml/rest/UpdatePdpThread.java:\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 126: if (!writePropertiesToStream(connection)) {\ntransactionEnded since it was started in line 107 ?\ndoes something need to be done here with the connection?\nOld code – connection obj – not called connect() yet. We create a new UpdatePdpThread for each pdp. Think we should close the loggingContext if it was created locally and not passed in.\n•\tFile ONAP-PAP-REST/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/xacml/rest/XACMLPapServlet.java:\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 121: \nI think marking them public will give sonars .. although not recall 100% sure.\nNew code – Fixed.\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 768: }\nnew code – Fixed.\n•\tFile ONAP-PAP-REST/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/xacml/rest/components/HandleIncomingNotifications.java:\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 125: case PDP_NOTIFICATION:\na lot of repeated code ..\nOld code – PlicyDbDao.java line: 616. Agree, it can be refactored.\n•\tFile ONAP-PAP-REST/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/xacml/rest/components/PolicyDBDao.java:\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 90: \nwhy the change to public? Don't think it is recommended if only used within the class ..\nNew code – since this class was broken up, these constants were needed in the new files and needed to be duplicated. So change to public and keep it in one place. Sonar doesn’t complain since constant.\n•\tFile ONAP-XACML/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/xacml/util/XACMLPolicyWriter.java:\no\tPatch Set #10, Line 175: JAXBElement<PolicySetType> policyElement = new ObjectFactory().createPolicySet(policy);\nRecommended practice is try-with-resources here. It is also recommended to close the string (which the try-with-resources will do for you) even though this is a byte array and you could get by without causing a memory leak.\nNew code – Agree, best practice. If it is ok,  I’m not changing for now since it would require more thorough testing. The current version works.  It seems consistent with existing policytype call from PolicyDbDaoTransactionInstance createPolicy() which does a IOUtils.closeQuietly()",
        "patchset_number": 11
      },
